HEADWORD: Cheirotherium
<hw>Chei`ro*the"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>chei`r</grk> hand + <grk>qhri`on</grk>
beast.]</ety> <fld>(Poleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of extinct animals, so
named from fossil footprints rudely resembling impressions of the human
hand, and believed to have been made by labyrinthodont reptiles. See
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

